When UN troops occupied Seoul for the third time, one American soldier met a Korean friend. Korean: Thank God you came again! And how did you manage it? - Very simple. When the communists come, I also say to them: well, thank God that you have come again! The soldier is offended: - For you, then, there is no difference? - Oh, no, there is a difference: I cannot tell the communists what I say to both sides same...